COMMENDATIONS. Commends and congratulates the Honorable Foster L. Campbell Jr.
on the occasion of fifty years of continuously holding elective office in Louisiana, first as
state senator and currently as Public Service Commissioner.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend and congratulate the Honorable Foster L. Campbell Jr. on the occasion of fifty
3 years of continuous elective service to the state of Louisiana, first as a state senator
4 and currently as Public Service Commissioner.
5 WHEREAS, Foster L. Campbell Jr. was born on January 6, 1947, in Shreveport,
6 Louisiana, and raised in Bossier Parish, where he developed the deep connection to rural
7 communities that would shape his public career; and
8 WHEREAS, he graduated from Bossier High School, attended Louisiana State
9 University, and earned a bachelor's degree in business and economics from Northwestern
10 State University; and
11 WHEREAS, Foster was a proud member of the Kappa Sigma fraternity at both LSU
12 and Northwestern, forming lifelong bonds with many fraternity brothers who would later
13 serve alongside him in elected office; and
14 WHEREAS, before entering public office, he worked as a schoolteacher at Plain
15 Dealing High School and Haughton High School in Bossier Parish, while also selling
16 agricultural products to support his young family; and
17 WHEREAS, in 1975, at the age of twenty-eight, Foster qualified for the open seat
18 in Senate District 36; and
