1 WHEREAS, throughout his fifty years in elected office, Foster has been recognized
2 for his steadfast advocacy for rural communities, his commitment to consumer fairness, his
3 plainspoken, and dedication to improving the quality of life for Louisiana citizens; and
4 WHEREAS, Foster's 1975 campaign slogan, "Works hard, talks straight, makes
5 sense", has continued to epitomize his life of public service; and
6 WHEREAS, he is an inductee of the Louisiana Political Hall of Fame and a recipient
7 of the Louisiana Democratic Party's Lifetime Achievement Award; and
8 WHEREAS, having been sworn in as a state senator during the nation's Bicentennial
9 year of 1976 and, due only to term limits, leaving the Public Service Commission at the end
10 of this Sesquicentennial year, Foster will have served in elected public office for a full
11 twenty percent of America's history; and
12 WHEREAS, it is entirely fitting and proper for the Senate of the Legislature of
13 Louisiana to honor one of its own, whose career reflects exceptional longevity, public
14 commitment, and unwavering service to the people of this state.
15 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
16 does hereby commend and congratulate Foster L. Campbell Jr. on the occasion of fifty years
17 of continuous elective service to the state of Louisiana, first as state senator and currently
18 as Public Service Commissioner.
19 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to
20 former state senator and current public service commissioner, the Honorable Foster L.
21 Campbell Jr.
